  "course_notes": "Topic: Ritual & Resistance in the Atlantic African Diaspora This graduate seminar will explore epistemic framings, ritual technologies, and discrete religious systems which undergird resistance movements and a range of sovereignty and liberatory projects in the Atlantic African diaspora from the 16th century to the present. Selected readings will include works written by cultural anthropologists, social and cultural historians, art historians, religious studies scholars, and other interdisciplinary specialists of the African diaspora.",
